A WANNABE terrorist who claimed he wanted to join Isis has been jailed for 16 months. Wannabe terrorist is sent to jail A WANNABE terrorist who claimed he wanted to join Isis has been jailed for 16 months.Abdul Hafes, 35, from Cambuslang, posted on Twitter he &quot;hates Shia and Kurds&quot; and said they should die. He said he wanted to join the terrorist group Isis.Hafes admitted at Glasgow Sheriff Court intending to stir up &shy;hatred on religious grounds and making racist remarks and was jailed for 16 months. 